	<body>
		<sec id="s1"><title/>
			<p>In <italic>PLoS Computational Biology,</italic> volume 2, issue 11: doi: <ext-link ext-link-type="doi" xlink:href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1371/journal.pcbi.0020121" xlink:type="simple">10.1371/journal.pcbi.0020121</ext-link></p>
			<p>In the author affiliation section, Dr. Iddo Friedberg should have been listed as a research scientist (instead of as a research assistant).</p>
			<p>In the section called <bold>Rule 1: Select a Position That Excites You</bold>, the sentence, “Just because the mentor is excited about the project does not mean that you will be six months into it.”, had the two words “that” and “you” switched.</p>
		</sec>
